<B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=5><P ALIGN="CENTER">Algebra Learning Plan 3</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER">The Straight Line</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"></P>
</FONT><FONT FACE="Arial"><P>Example</P>
</B>
<P>A pharmaceutical company calculate the total cost, to the customer, for a particular drug using the relationship</P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER">C = 5n + 1000</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"></P>
<P>where C is total cost (£) and n is number of tablets supplied.</P>

<P>It would be possible to set up a table of values  which gives an indication of cost depending on number of tablets purchased.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P></FONT>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><TABLE BORDER CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=7 WIDTH=514>
<TR><TD WIDTH="7%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P>n</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">0</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">50</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">100</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="11%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">150</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="11%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">200</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">250</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">300</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">350</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">400</FONT></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH="7%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P>C</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">1000</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">1250</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">1500</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="11%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">1750</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="11%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">2000</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">2250</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">2500</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">1750</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT FACE="Arial"><P ALIGN="RIGHT">3000</FONT></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</P>

<FONT FACE="Arial">
<P>These values could be plotted on a graph to highlight the steady increase in cost.</P>

<P><img src="K:\calmat\scalmat\plans\gif\image92.gif"></P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Using the graph it would now be possible to estimate the cost for a given value of n.</P>

<P>Notice that this relationship produces a straight <B>line </B>graph.   It is a <B>line</B>ar relationship (The power on both variables is 1.   Remember  C = 5n + 1000 could be written C<SUP>1</SUP> = 5n<SUP>1</SUP> + 1000.)</P>

<P>Remind yourself of the features of straight line graphs by spending time in <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 41 a~?">1-41 section a</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 41 b 0~?">section b</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 41 c 0~?">section c</a>.   Try <a href="launch.htm#q0594">q0594</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0377">q0377</a>.</P></FONT></BODY>
